theorem Topology.interiorClosureInteriorClosure_eq_interiorClosure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- First inclusion: `⊆`
  have h₁ : interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    apply interior_mono
    apply closure_mono
    exact (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
  -- Second inclusion: `⊇`
  have h₂ : interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
    -- `interior (closure A)` is open and contained in its closure.
    have hSub : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      intro x hx
      exact subset_closure hx
    have hOpen : IsOpen (interior (closure A)) := isOpen_interior
    exact interior_maximal hSub hOpen
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.closure_inter_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  -- We show each component of the intersection separately.
  intro x hx
  have hx₁ : x ∈ closure A := by
    -- `A` is contained in `A ∩ B` after intersecting with `B`, so its closure is too.
    have hSub : A ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact ⟨hy, by
        -- Any element of `A` may not necessarily lie in `B`; use `subset_closure`
        -- and the fact that `closure` is monotone instead.
        have : y ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := subset_closure ?h
        simpa using this⟩
    have : closure A ⊆ closure (A ∩ B) := closure_mono hSub
    have : x ∈ closure A := by
      have : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := hx
      exact this
    exact this
  have hx₂ : x ∈ closure B := by
    -- Symmetric argument for `B`.
    have hSub : B ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact ⟨by
        -- Similar to the previous case, use `subset_closure` to justify membership.
        have : y ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := subset_closure ?h
        simpa using this, hy⟩
    have : closure B ⊆ closure (A ∩ B) := closure_mono hSub
    have : x ∈ closure B := by
      have : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := hx
      exact this
    exact this
  exact ⟨hx₁, hx₂⟩

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_inter_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∩ B)) ⊆ interior (closure A) ∩ interior (closure B) := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ interior (closure A) := by
    have hMono : closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure A := closure_mono Set.inter_subset_left
    exact (interior_mono hMono) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ interior (closure B) := by
    have hMono : closure (A ∩ B) ⊆ closure B := closure_mono Set.inter_subset_right
    exact (interior_mono hMono) hx
  exact ⟨hxA, hxB⟩

theorem Topology.closureInterior_inter_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∩ B)) ⊆ closure (interior A) ∩ closure (interior B) := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ closure (interior A) := by
    have hMono : interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ interior A := interior_mono Set.inter_subset_left
    have hClosureMono : closure (interior (A ∩ B)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      closure_mono hMono
    exact hClosureMono hx
  have hxB : x ∈ closure (interior B) := by
    have hMono : interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ interior B := interior_mono Set.inter_subset_right
    have hClosureMono : closure (interior (A ∩ B)) ⊆ closure (interior B) :=
      closure_mono hMono
    exact hClosureMono hx
  exact ⟨hxA, hxB⟩

theorem Topology.interior_subset_interiorClosure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  simpa using interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
